<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,387,990]" pageId="12" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,783,809]" pageId="12" pageNumber="91">Remarks:</emphasis>
Present report is the first record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1823" box="[742,852,783,809]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Anereuthina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="renosa">
<emphasis box="[742,852,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="91">A. renosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[972,1155,783,809]" name="India" pageId="12" pageNumber="91">Nicobar Islands</collectingCountry>
. The distribution of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[271,329,819,845]" name="India" pageId="12" pageNumber="91">India</collectingCountry>
is documented on www.mothsofindia.org through photographic evidence from South Garo Hills, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,275,855,881]" country="India" name="Meghalaya" pageId="12" pageNumber="91">Meghalaya</collectingRegion>
and Port Blair, Andaman Islands (Sondhi 
<emphasis box="[744,793,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="91">et al</emphasis>
. 2021). But we could not review any published document regarding its distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[460,521,891,917]" name="India" pageId="12" pageNumber="91">India</collectingCountry>
. The species is recorded between wide altitudinal ranges from lowland dipterocarp forest at 
<quantity box="[251,324,927,954]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="91" unit="m" value="150.0">150 m</quantity>
in Nicobar (present study), to uphill montane forest at 
<quantity box="[951,1037,927,954]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6179999999999999" pageId="12" pageNumber="91" unit="m" value="1618.0">1618 m</quantity>
altitude in Borneo, 
<collectingCountry box="[1265,1368,927,953]" name="Malaysia" pageId="12" pageNumber="91">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." pageId="12" pageNumber="91" refId="ref9467" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2005) The Moths of Borneo: Parts 15 &amp; 16; Family Noctuidae: Catocalinae. Malayan Nature Journal, Southdene Sdn Bhd., 529 pp., 28 pls." type="book" year="2005">Holloway 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
